<table>
    <caption class="text-xl font-semibold">
        WCAG 2.1 Mobile Checklist
    </caption>
    <thead>
    <tr>
        <th scope="col">Success Criteria</th>
        <th scope="col">#</th>
        <th scope="col">LVL</th>
        <th scope="col">Guideline</th>
        <th scope="col">Mobile Accessibility QA Test Method</th>
    </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Non-text Content</th>
        <td>1.1.1</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Text Alternatives</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Set screen reader focus to each non-text content element including images, buttons, form controls,
                    iframes, and audio/video.&nbsp;
                </li>
                <li>Check that accessible name spoken is a short, accurate description of the non-text content, but does
                    not identify its type. E.g. a play button should have the label “Play” but not its role “button”
                    included in the label. Check that you don’t hear output similar to “Play Button, button”. &nbsp;
                    &nbsp;
                </li>
                <li>Check that role spoken correctly describes element’s state, behavior, or usage. E.g. check that
                    buttons have a button role and images have an image role.&nbsp;
                </li>
                <li>Check that any required accessible description information is also spoken.</li>
                <li>Check that adjustable elements like sliders have the correct value like “50%”. Adjust the values and
                    check that the screen reader speaks the correct value.
                </li>
                <li>Check that purely decorative images are not focusable by the keyboard or screen reader.&nbsp;</li>
                <li>Check that that custom views such as star rating widgets speak an accurate label.&nbsp;</li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Audio-only and Video-only (Prerecorded)</th>
        <td>1.2.1</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Time-based Media</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Check that information presented in audio-only format has a text transcript.</li>
                <li>Check that information presented in video-only format has a either an audio equivalent or a text
                    transcript.
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Captions (Prerecorded)</th>
        <td>1.2.2&nbsp;</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Time-based Media</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Enable closed captions under Settings.</li>
                <li>Play videos.&nbsp;</li>
                <li>Check that videos include synchronized captions.</li>
                <li>Check that captions are accurate.&nbsp;</li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Audio Description or Media Alternative (Prerecorded)</th>
        <td>1.2.3</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Time-based Media</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Play videos.&nbsp;</li>
                <li>Language button should appear if closed audio descriptions track included.</li>
                <li>Activate Language button, select audio descriptions track.</li>
                <li>Check that audio descriptions are accurate.&nbsp;</li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Captions (Live)</th>
        <td>1.2.4</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Time-based Media</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Check that live captions are provided for all real-time audio/video presentations.</li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Audio Description (Prerecorded)</th>
        <td>1.2.5</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Time-based Media</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Play videos.&nbsp;</li>
                <li>Language button should appear if closed audio descriptions track included.</li>
                <li>Activate Language button, select audio descriptions track.</li>
                <li>Check that audio descriptions are accurate.&nbsp;</li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Info and Relationships</th>
        <td>1.3.1</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Adaptable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate through all semantic HTML elements using screen reader gestures or keyboard
                    commands.&nbsp;
                </li>
                <li>Set screen reader focus to Headings, Lists, Tables and check that they correctly coded with semantic
                    HTML.
                </li>
                <li>If you cannot set focus to an item that appears to be a Heading element when using heading quick
                    navigation commands then is is not coded with semantic HTML.
                </li>
                <li>Navigate between row and columns inside data table cells with the screen reader and check that the
                    correct row and column headers are spoken.
                </li>
                <li>Check that the &lt;legend&gt; text is spoken for each &lt;input&gt; within a &lt;fieldset&gt; when
                    the screen reader sets focus to an input in the group.
                </li>
                <li>Use Landmark navigation to check that you can jump between the visually distinct Header, Navigation,
                    Main Content, and Footer regions of the page.
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Meaningful Sequence</th>
        <td>1.3.2</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Adaptable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Swipe through all elements on the screen from top to bottom and check that the reading order matches
                    the visual presentation order.
                </li>
                <li>Check that content is read in an order that does not disrupt the meaning.</li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Sensory Characteristics</th>
        <td>1.3.3</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Adaptable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Check that instructions provided for using the app do not rely solely on visual or audio-only
                    information.&nbsp;
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <th scope="row">Orientation <small class="block text-xs text-green-600">New in 2.1</small></th>
        <td>1.3.4</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Adaptable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Check that layout follows device orientation by rotating the device.</li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <th scope="row">Identify Input Purpose <small class="block text-xs text-green-600">New in 2.1</small></th>
        <td>1.3.5</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Adaptable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Open the application and ensure that the virtual keyboard is enabled (built-in keyboard for the
                    phone).
                </li>
                <li>Place your cursor inside the input field and ensure that the keyboard matches the appropriate input
                    type.
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Use of Color</th>
        <td>1.4.1</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Distinguishable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Set device to use grayscale colors only in accessibility settings.</li>
                <li>Check that color alone is not used as the only means of conveying information.&nbsp;</li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Audio Control</th>
        <td>1.4.2</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Distinguishable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Check that any audio that plays automatically for more than 3 seconds has a method to pause or stop
                    the audio, or a method to control its audio volume independent from the system volume.
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Contrast (Minimum)</th>
        <td>1.4.3</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Distinguishable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Use a color contrast analyzer testing tool to check that text is not too light when used on a light
                    background or too dark when used on a dark background.&nbsp;
                </li>
                <li>Logos and text that are purely decorative do not need contrast testing.&nbsp;</li>
                <li>Disabled controls don't need to meet contrast requirements.</li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Resize text</th>
        <td>1.4.4</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Distinguishable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Pinch-to-zoom should be able to increase the text size.</li>
                <li>If pinch-to-zoom is not working then another method must be available to resizes text.</li>
                <li>Enable Large Text sizes under accessibility settings and test native app to check that text can
                    enlarge.
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Images of Text</th>
        <td>1.4.5</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Distinguishable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Images of text should not be used.</li>
                <li>Set focus to any images of text.&nbsp;</li>
                <li>Check that all images of text have the exact, correct text alternative.&nbsp;</li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Reflow<small class="block text-xs text-green-600">New in 2.1</small></th>
        <td>1.4.10</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Distinguishable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    Enable Large Text sizes under accessibility settings and test native app to check that text can
                    enlarge.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Check that app don't alter scroll interaction (scroll both ways).
                </li>
                <li>
                    Check that content do not disappear or is unavailable on reflow.
                </li>
            </ol>
            <small class="text-xs">
                Content which requires two-dimensional layout for usage or meaning cannot reflow without losing meaning, and is therefore out of scope of this Success Criterion.
            </small>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Non-text Contrast<small class="block text-xs text-green-600">New in 2.1</small></th>
        <td>1.4.11</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Distinguishable</td>
        <td>
            <ul>
                <li>Use a color contrast analyzer testing tool to check that text is not too light when used on a light
                    background or too dark when used on a dark background.
                </li>
                <li>This success criterion does not require that controls have a visual boundary indicating the hit
                    area, but if the visual indicator of the control is the only way to identify the control, then that
                    indicator must have sufficient contrast.
                </li>
                <li>If text (or an icon) within a button or placeholder text inside a text input is visible and there is
                    no visual indication of the hit area then the Success Criterion is passed.
                </li>
                <li>Disabled controls don't need to meet contrast requirements.</li>
            </ul>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <th scope="row">Text Spacing<small class="block text-xs text-green-600">New in 2.1</small></th>
        <td>1.4.12</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Distinguishable</td>
        <td>
            <p>To comply with this success criterion, it is needed to let users adjust the following things:</p>
            <ol class="my-4">
                <li>The line height to at least 1.5 times the font size</li>
                <li>The spacing between paragraphs to at least 2 times the font size</li>
                <li>The letter spacing to at least 0.12 times the font size</li>
                <li>The spacing of words to at least 0.16 times the font size</li>
            </ol>
            <p>Example of css code to match previous requirements:</p>
            <pre>
                    <code class="text-xs">
* {
    line-height: 1.5 !important;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em !important;
    word-spacing: 0.16em !important;
}

p {
    margin-bottom: 2em !important;
}
                    </code>
                </pre>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Content on Hover or Focus<small class="block text-xs text-green-600">New in 2.1</small></th>
        <td>1.4.13</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Distinguishable</td>
        <td>
            <p>Navigate through the app using a keyboard.If additional content appears due to a hover or focus state check that:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>content is dismissible without moving the cursor</li>
                <li>content is operable moving focus the component that triggered change to the additional content</li>
                <li>content is operable until user remove focus from additional content or from trigger component</li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Keyboard</th>
        <td>2.1.1</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Keyboard Accessible</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>For iOS, navigate the app and activate all user interface controls using VoiceOver and a Keyboard.
                </li>
                <li>For Android, navigate the app and activate all user interface controls using a Keyboard only without
                    TalkBack running.
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <th scope="row">No Keyboard Trap</th>
        <td>2.1.2</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Keyboard Accessible</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate through all elements in the app and check that focus is never trapped.&nbsp;</li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <th scope="row">Timing Adjustable</th>
        <td>2.2.1</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Enough Time</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate through the app but leave the app idle for a period of time until the time-out activates.&nbsp;</li>
                <li>Check that there is a warning before you are kicked out and that you are allowed to extend your
                    session before being logged out. Or check that you can adjust the time limit settings to at least 10
                    times longer than the default.&nbsp;
                </li>
                <li>Time out extensions do not apply to real time exceptions like auctions or timed tests.&nbsp;</li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Pause, Stop, Hide</th>
        <td>2.2.2</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Enough Time</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Check that moving, blinking, scrolling, or auto-updating content is able to be paused, stopped, or
                    hidden.&nbsp;
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Three Flashes or Below Threshold</th>
        <td>2.3.1</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Seizures</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Check that the app has no elements that flash more than three times per second.&nbsp;</li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Bypass Blocks</th>
        <td>2.4.1</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Navigable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Check that there is a method such as a skip link or WAI-ARIA landmarks that allow the user to bypass
                    blocks of content that are repeated on multiple screens.
                </li>
                <li>Use Landmarks quick navigation commands to bypass blocks of content. Check that you can use
                    landmarks to skip over the navigation directly to the main content.&nbsp;
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Page Titled</th>
        <td>2.4.2</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Navigable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Check that each screen in the app has a useful &amp; unique title.&nbsp;</li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Focus Order</th>
        <td>2.4.3</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Navigable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate through all elements in the app using gestures or the keyboard and check that they are read
                    in the correct order.&nbsp;
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Link Purpose (In Context)</th>
        <td>2.4.4</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Navigable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Set focus to every link and button, check that its accessible name spoken to the screen reader makes
                    sense.
                </li>
                <li>Check that the purpose of each link or button can be determined based on its label text alone or its
                    label text together with its <a
                            href="http://www.w3.org/TR/UNDERSTANDING-WCAG20/navigation-mechanisms-refs.html#pdlinkcontextdef">programmatically
                        determined link context</a>.
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Multiple Ways</th>
        <td>2.4.5</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Navigable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Check that there are multiple ways to find content within an app by using a search feature, table of
                    contents, site map, or linking to all parts of app from the home page.&nbsp;
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Headings and Labels</th>
        <td>2.4.6</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Navigable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Check that headings used for organizing content and labels for user interface controls and form
                    inputs describe their topic or purpose.&nbsp;
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Focus Visible</th>
        <td>2.4.7</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Navigable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate through all elements of the app using a keyboard and check that focus is always visible.&nbsp;</li>
                <li>Check that the currently focused element is always visible on screen.</li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Pointer Gestures<small class="block text-xs text-green-600">New in 2.1</small></th>
        <td>2.5.1</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Input Modalities</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Check if the app has functionalities based on gestures (multi-pointer or path-based).</li>
                <li>Check if such functionalities can be operated by a single pointer or are essentials.</li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <th scope="row">Pointer Cancellation<small class="block text-xs text-green-600">New in 2.1</small></th>
        <td>2.5.2</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Input Modalities</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Check if the app has single pointer functionalities</li>
                <li>For each functionality check that at least one of the following propositions is true:
                    <ol>
                        <li>The down-event of the pointer is not used to execute any part of the function</li>
                        <li>The completion of the function is on the up-event and a mechanism is available to abort the
                            function before completion
                        </li>
                        <li>The up-event reverse any outcome of the preceding down event</li>
                        <li>Completing the function on the down-event is essential</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <th scope="row">Label in Name<small class="block text-xs text-green-600">New in 2.1</small></th>
        <td>2.5.3</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Input Modalities</td>
        <td><p>Using Talkback or VoiceOver navigate the app's inputs and check announced name matches visual text</p></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <th scope="row">Motion Actuation<small class="block text-xs text-green-600">New in 2.1</small></th>
        <td>2.5.4</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Input Modalities</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Check if the app has device motion or user motion functionalities</li>
                <li>For each functionality check that functionality can be operated from a user interface and motion
                    detection can be disabled to prevent accidental actuation unless when:
                    <ol>
                        <li>The motion is used to operate functionality through an accessibility supported interface
                        </li>
                        <li>The motion is essential for the function and doing so would invalidate the activity</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Language of Page</th>
        <td>3.1.1</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Readable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Set screen reader speech settings to default language.</li>
                <li>Set focus to page content and the screen reader should speak text in the proper speech language
                    synthesizer.&nbsp;
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Language of Parts</th>
        <td>3.1.2</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Readable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Set screen reader speech settings to default language.</li>
                <li>Set focus to parts of the page with a different language and the screen reader should speak text in
                    the proper speech language synthesizer, e.g. lang="es" will speak with a Spanish screen reader voice
                    rather than English.
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">On Focus</th>
        <td>3.2.1</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Predictable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Set focus to all components of the app and check that when a component receives focus that it does
                    not cause a <a
                            href="http://www.w3.org/TR/UNDERSTANDING-WCAG20/consistent-behavior-receive-focus.html#context-changedef">change
                        of context</a>.&nbsp;
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">On Input</th>
        <td>3.2.2</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Predictable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Change the settings of all user interface components and check that does not automatically cause of
                    a change of context unless the user has been warned of that behavior before using the component.&nbsp;
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Consistent Navigation</th>
        <td>3.2.3</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Predictable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate through all screens of the app and check that the app’s internal navigation occurs in the
                    same relative order and is consistent.&nbsp;
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Consistent Identification</th>
        <td>3.2.4</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Predictable</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate through all screens of the app and check that the user interface components are identified
                    consistently.&nbsp;
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Error Identification</th>
        <td>3.3.1</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Input Assistance</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Submit forms in the app using blank and incorrect data.</li>
                <li>Check that errors are identified, described in text, and spoken by the screen reader.</li>
                <li>Set focus to inputs that have errors and check that the error messages are spoken by the screen
                    reader.&nbsp;
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Labels or Instructions</th>
        <td>3.3.2</td>
        <td>A</td>
        <td>Input Assistance</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Set focus to each text input control and check that the spoken label provides instructions for user
                    input.
                </li>
                <li>Set focus to form controls that require specifically formatted input and check that all instructions
                    for correctly entering the text are spoken by the screen reader.
                </li>
                <li>Check that labels and instructions are always visible to the sighted user also.</li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Error Suggestion</th>
        <td>3.3.3</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Input Assistance</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>Set focus to an input that has been incorrectly formatted or was left blank and is in error.&nbsp;
                </li>
                <li>Check that an example or suggestion of a correct input and its format is visible and spoken by the
                    screen reader.&nbsp;
                </li>
            </ol>
        </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>

        <th scope="row">Error Prevention (Legal, Financial, Data)</th>
        <td>3.3.4</td>
        <td>AA</td>
        <td>Input Assistance</td>
        <td>
            <ol>
                <li>This success criterion applies to apps with actions that cause legal commitments, financial
                    transactions, that modify or delete user-controllable data in data storage systems, or submits user
                    test responses.&nbsp;
                </li>
                <li>Test the app to check that submissions are reversible, that the user can check the date for input
                    errors with a chance to correct them, or that information is reviewed, confirmed, and corrected
                    before finalizing the submission.&nbsp;
                </li>
            </ol>
